<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,713,918]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,749,774]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Two strong fronto-orbital setae. Genital fork distinctly elongate, reaching sternite 
<number box="[1253,1269,750,773]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" value="7.0">7</number>
; arm elongate, nearly twice as long as base of genital fork, narrow and strongly incurved on distal 
<number box="[1107,1118,786,810]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1130,1145,786,810]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" value="3.0">3</number>
; basal tubercle small, not contiguous, medial tubercle small but distinctive. Distiphallus shorter than phallapodeme. Pregonite lobed apically. Postgonite with 
<number box="[333,347,858,882]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" value="1.0">1</number>
apical seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1089,893,918]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="discussion">
